00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:53,557
Take 500 grams of chicken. To this, add 1 tsp shahi jeera (caraway seeds), 1 tsp freshly crushed ginger garlic paste, 1/4 cup fried onions, and 1/2 cup chopped coriander.

3
00:00:56,426 --> 00:01:26,414
Now add 1 tbsp red chili powder, 1 tsp cumin powder, 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp garam masala, 1 tsp coriander powder, and salt. Mix everything well. Then add 1/4 cup yogurt and mix thoroughly.

4
00:01:26,617 --> 00:01:54,308
Take half a biryani leaf (bay leaf), 4-5 cardamoms, and a small cinnamon stick and massage everything well into the chicken. Now refrigerate this for one hour. Meanwhile, boil 2 liters of water. To this add 5–6 cloves...

5
00:01:55,978 --> 00:02:20,194
Soak 1.5 cups of basmati rice in water. (Repeated words in original seem like a speech glitch or stutter, so translated just once.)

6
00:02:25,712 --> 00:02:53,894
In the rice, add 2 tbsp chopped mint, two pinches of garam masala powder, 3 tbsp ghee, and 3 tbsp fried onions. Add 1 tbsp of the hot water that was soaked with saffron.

7
00:02:54,028 --> 00:03:17,872
Now turn off the stove and let it sit for 15 to 25 minutes before serving. That’s when the perfect flavor develops. Did you see? That’s the perfect Hyderabadi Chicken Dum Biryani!

